orithm changes for Engineering team use\nCollaborate with product owners, designers, and other dev team members\nParticipate in all scrum activities\n\nWho We\'re Looking For:\n\n5+ years of data science, machine learning, advanced analytics\nExtensive experience in applying Data Science / ML in production to build data-driven products for solving business problems\nStrong coding skills in general purpose languages (Java/Python) and familiarity with software engineering principles around testing, code reviews, and deployment. Bonus points for C++ background.\nStrong knowledge of common clustering, classification, and regression models.\nExperience collaborating and understanding needs of various stakeholders (Product Management and Engineering)\nMS or PH.D in quantitative fields (e.g. Statistics, Math, Computer Science, Economics)\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nPay: From $200,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n\n401(k)\nDental insurance\nFlexible spending account\nHealth insurance\nHealth savings account\nLife insurance\nPaid time off\nProfessional development assistance\nReferral program\nVision insurance\n\nSchedule:\n\nMonday to Friday\n\nCOVID-19 considerations:\nFull COVID vaccinations required, additional office safety protocols in place at office locations.\n\nApplication Question(s):\n\nPlease provide examples of 3 specific business problems solved with your analytical solutions and discuss both approach and outcomes. Please, no company names or confidential information.\n\nEducation:\n\nMaster\'s (Required)\n\nExperience:\n\nData science: 5 years (Required)\nMachine learning: 5 years (Required)\nC++: 3 years (Preferred)\nProduct development: 3 years (Required)\nPython: 5 years (Required)\n\nWork Location:\n\nFully Remote\n\nWork Location: Remote','https://indeed.com/pagead/clk?mo=r&ad=-6NYlbfkN0C4ExUy6zKKLYxakEvUKmvHOdi77s4eMH7Omr_DhcSkTLlzUjYz7sSoEXsDT7sAYzFh3_18tpoRrID3GbqemwFNCPaU6I3w1COxkL_vwUPoVJCKl4i7k0SQdLVqv19fLsIkQAZe9WSQYVO60Jqp9tM7B7lfe4Rnr7tFphvfEsUBg_DbFeJk7btXY5CyLA2mIxOHOA7O2Y5y8t0yl','indeed'),(415,'Junior Data Scientist','United States',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','Company Description\n\n\nMeasured Analytics and Insurance is a high-growth Insurtech based in Salt Lake City, Utah. We\'re building smarter cyber insurance products designed specifically for the future of digital risk powered by artificial intelligence and machine learning. At Measured, we passionately believe in the power of data to drive better outcomes for our customers.\n\n\n\nJob Description\n\n\nWe\'re looking for a Junior Data Scientist who will join our Data Science team that is building the best-in-class cyber insurance risk modeling platform. The ideal candidate will have education or equivalent professional experience in analyzing large data sets, familiarity with different ML modeling techniques, and hands-on experience with ML frameworks and libraries. If you are passionate about transforming data into actionable insights, we want to talk to you.\n\nThe things we\'d like you to do:\n\nBuild tools to automate data collection and set up data pipelines that populate our Data Lake\n\nAssist in tuning and validation of cyber-insurance risk models\n\nCreate reports and data visualizations to present analytic results\n\nResearch new data sets and modeling techniques to improve our predictive modeling efficacy\n\n\n\nQualifications\n\n\nBS/MS in Data Science or equivalent experience\n\nExperience working with Machine Learning software and languages including Python, Jupyter notebooks, and ML/Data Analytics libraries\n\nWorking knowledge of Data Engineering tools on AWS such as Glue, Athena, S3\n\nFamiliarity with Agile software development process\n\n\nAdditional Information\n\n\nGet in on the ground floor of a new & growing company.\n\nSignificant career advancement opportunities in an expanding operation.\n\nThe chance to have direct input on shaping company strategy and direction\n\nAutonomy while being supported by skilled teammates\n\nCompetitive salary and equity grants\n\nAbility to work remotely','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=bfb0bf7a91dfca3b&fccid=180448108da5f0aa&vjs=3','indeed'),(416,'Data Science & Analytics','United States',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','As much as you’re a master at rigorous mining, culling and interpretation of big data, you’re equally at task to glean small but meaningful data insights and making it pop in multiple data visualization platforms.','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=11d0e53098f06688&fccid=be78c43e20f71cf5&vjs=3','indeed'),(417,'Data Scientist','United States','University of Utah',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','ABOUT US\nWe create global impact by combining impact investing & innovative finance, data science, policy\nentrepreneurship, community engagement, and impact storytelling. This Sorenson Impact Methodology™ translates inspiration into impact and helps social entrepreneurs and organizations articulate, measure, and expand their impact. Students are integrated into all our work. We operate an impact investing practice for our own fund and as a manager of an outside fund; we annually host one of the largest gatherings in the impact space; we have a thriving Data, Policy and Performance Innovation advisory practice and a world-class creative shop.\n\nThe Sorenson Impact Center strongly encourages diverse applicants (please circulate widely), especially those who self-identify as Black, Native or Indigenous, People of Color, LGBTQIA+, non-binary, living with disabilities, neurodivergent, young, speak English as a second language, and others from overlooked / underestimated communities.\n\nJob Overview:\nConducts advanced statistical analyses of qualitative and quantitative data and interprets results. Works on independent projects as part of the data team and applies appropriate data science techniques to provide insights and answers to social impact issues. Effectively communicates data analyses to a variety of audiences, both technical and non-technical.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n1. Oversees/conducts statistical analyses, employing methods of descriptive statistics, multivariate analysis, regression analysis, and other statistical modeling techniques appropriate for the client’s needs.\n2. Formats data for statistical analysis.\n3. Presents statistical findings to a lay audience.\n4. Writes reports and creates dashboards and data visualizations for clients.\n5. May devise methods and procedures for collecting data.\n6. May travel to a variety of sites within and outside the University to coordinate projects.\n7. May supervise junior staff/students.\n\nThis job description is not designed to contain or be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities and qualifications required of employees assigned to the job.\n\nWork Environment and Level of Frequency that may be required\n\nNearly Continuously: Office environment.\n\nPhysical Requirements and Level of Frequency that may be required\n\nNearly Continuously: Sitting, hearing, listening, talking.\n\nOften: Repetitive hand motion (such as typing), walking.\n\nSeldom: Bending, reaching overhead.\n\nMinimum Qualifications\n\nBachelor’s degree in a related field or equivalency; plus four years related research experience, and demonstrated human relation and effective communication skills also required.\n\nA Master’s degree in a related field is preferred.\n\nApplicants must demonstrate the potential ability to perform the essential functions of the job as outlined in the position description.\n\nPreferences\n\nPreference will be given to candidates who exhibit the following:\n\nExperience in managing projects among diverse stakeholders.\nA degree in data science, statistics, business, public policy, or a related field. Master’s or PhD preferred.\nData engineering or analysis experience required.\nStrong analytical, writing, and communication skills.\nProficiency in a programming language, such as R or Python (R preferred).\nType Benefited Staff Special Instructions Summary','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=c02fa894e6b61398&fccid=6328b27691d3fdc3&vjs=3','indeed'),(418,'Statistician / Data Scientist','United States','Qualis Corporation',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','Qualis Corporation is seeking an experienced Statistician/Data Scientist to support test documentation and data collection services for the West Desert Test Center (WDTC) at Dugway Proving Ground (DPG), UT. This is a full-time position.\n\nEssential Functions\n\nWork closely with the Government POC and the customer to identify the appropriate statistical and visualization analysis for each project.\nUsing supporting data and analysis, the Statistician/Data Scientist will provide technical guidance and recommendations to test directors and other test team members throughout WDTC for development of test design plans; data collection, reduction and analysis plans; test methodology; and final report preparation.\n\nMinimum Requirements\n\nBachelor’s degree in statistics or data science and 3-5 years minimum experience.\nDemonstrated experience in task management and interpersonal communication skills.\nDemonstrated ability to be innovative and adapt to changing program and customer requirements.\nStrong problem-solving skills.\nHave a strong statistical background and be responsible for the development of R and/or Python code supporting statistical and graphical analyses.\nDemonstrated skill in providing high-level briefings.\nDemonstrated experience in physical sciences, chemical sciences, biological sciences, or engineering, with experience in design and analysis of field tests, physical laboratory tests, and/or chemical warfare/CB development.\nChemical or biological laboratory experience is also desirable.\n\nClearance\n\nMust be able to obtain and maintain a DoD Secret security clearance.\n\n\n\nEqual Opportunity Employer/M/F/Vet/Disabled and a Participant in E-Verify','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=4430e9bb586ec085&fccid=9042cf9c63586136&vjs=3','indeed'),(419,'Data Scientist','United States','ReliaQuest, LLC.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','ReliaQuest is looking for passionate Data Science professionals to join our team. This role will drive the creation, testing and deployment of cutting edge security technology to enterprise customers across the globe. You will build, design, and get tools to market tht will mature and advance the information security field. It is a great opportunity to advance your career in a fast-growing organization by creating new services/capabilities that do not exist today in the Cyber Security industry.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nSelect and engineer features from a wide variety of data sets\nBuild and optimize classifiers using machine learning techniques\nProcessing, cleaning, and verifying the integrity of the data used for analysis\nCreating anomaly detection systems and tracking their performance\nIntegrate model inference into multiple diverse data pipelines\nPerform code reviews and mentor peers\n\nQualifications:\n\nUnderstanding of machine learning techniques and algorithms\nExperience with common data science toolkits\nKnowledge of Sagemaker,Apache Spark, Tensorflow, Pandas, NumPy, Jupyter Notebooks, Keras\nPractical experience using NLP\nProficiency in creation of dashboards and visualizations\nKnowledge of a combination of the following scripting and programming languages: Java, C, C++, C#, Python, Javascript, R\nPreferred experience with Elasticsearch, GPU accelerated operations,log ingestion\nDemonstrable mastery of statistics. Additional skills in linear algebra and/or calculus beneficial\nBachelor’s in Computer Science/Engineering, Mathematics, Physics (or Equivalent Experience)\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nWork Location: Multiple Locations','https://indeed.com/company/ReliaQuest,-LLC./jobs/Data-Scientist-0f25929654d8912d?fccid=399ca3c01ad9c434&vjs=3','indeed'),(420,'Data Scientist','United States',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','At MarketDial we equip our clients with the easiest-to-use and most accurate solution to conduct offline A/B testing. In short, we provide our clients with the tools they need to set up statistically robust trials to test various initiatives across their business. This allows them to learn quickly and have greater confidence in the initiatives they ultimately decide to roll out - saving time, money, and energy. To date, our software has allowed our clients across the retail, grocery, c-store, restaurant, and manufacturing markets to make sophisticated multi-million dollar marketing, pricing, staffing, and operational decisions through offline A/B testing.\n\nWe pride ourselves on offering our clients unparalleled support to ensure their success with MarketDial. We are currently seeking a Data Scientist to uniquely support our clients in the U.S. and abroad.\n\nJob description:\n\nThis role has a variety of responsibilities spanning engagement with MarketDial users and senior executives/project sponsors. A sample of responsibilities include:\n\nSupport users in end to end process of testing, from designing the ideal test to meet their business need, to understanding the business implications of the test outcome\nAnalyze data and create novel analytical solutions to answer business questions\nHost regular training sessions to equip new users with the skills to effectively use MarketDial\nResearch statistical/ML methodologies to solve client problems and develop the MarketDial product\nEngage key stakeholders to increase MarketDial awareness across business units, including promoting MarketDial at various business town halls\nStrategize with senior leaders to embed MarketDial into the broader testing governance/framework of their business\nOnboard new teams/brands through effective collaboration with project sponsors and technical stakeholders\nEffectively gather user feedback to understand opportunities to enhance our product, and work with the MarketDial leadership team to incorporate feedback into product development\nProduce high quality materials (powerpoint, etc.) to engage with clients (users and senior executives) on test outcomes and broader partnership objectives\n\nThe ideal candidate should:\n\nBe comfortable working and communicating with senior executives as well as business analysts\nBe knowledgeable in applying of statistical and ML methodologies using tools like Python to solve real-world problems\nBe able to work independently and drive projects with limited direction (be comfortable with being uncomfortable)\nBe open to travel as needed to meet client needs\n\nNice to have:\n\nA background in retail analytics or management consulting is preferred but not required\nExperience with/technical skills of Python, SQL, R, SAS, or the likes is highly desirable\nAn advanced degree (Ph\'D, Masters) in an analytical discipline is preferred but not required\nAdept with translating concepts and analytics into an effective presentation appropriate for various audiences\nProject management experience or skills highly desirable\n\nSome of the benefits you will enjoy:\n\nCompetitive pay and stock option grants.\nFully-covered healthcare, as well as a company-funded HRA account to pay for all out of pocket costs.\nUnlimited vacation policy.\nGenerous parental leave.\nRegular free meals.\nFully stocked kitchen.\nOpen, transparent office and culture.\nContinuing education/tuition reimbursement program.\nTransportation benefits and reimbursement program.\n\nData Scientist will be located in the Salt Lake City, Utah area and report to the Chief Data Scientist who sits in SLC.','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=59454e471fe5c70d&fccid=c487856e779406d1&vjs=3','indeed'),(421,'Data Engineer - AI and Data Operations - Remote','United States','MarketStar',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','If you are a current employee who is interested in applying to this position, please navigate to the internal Careers site to apply.\n\nData Engineer - AI and Data Operations - Remote\n\nLocation: Remote\n\nAbout MarketStar:\nRated as one of the Salt Lake Tribune’s Top Workplaces in 2019 and 2020, MarketStar is one of Northern Utah’s largest private employers and has offices in Ogden, Salt Lake City, and Dublin, Ireland. Our employees have helped launch, sell, and support thousands of products and services on behalf of the biggest and brightest companies in the world!\n\nWe are excited to have you apply to work with us! “You Belong” is one of the MarketStar values and we look forward to you finding belonging and purpose here with us. Another MarketStar value is “We Care” which means that we care about you, your career and your family. We look forward to the possibility of having you on our team!\n\nMarketStar Benefits and Perks:\n• Childcare Reimbursement – 50% up to $5000 annually\n• Healthcare Coverage: Medical, dental, vision (First day of following month)\n• 401k Match: 100% pre-tax match on the first 3%, 50% pre-tax match on the following 2%\n• Paid Time Off: 4.5 weeks total PTO + 7 Paid Holidays\n• Paid Family Maternity/Paternity Leave: Up to 6 weeks (eligible after 1 year of employment)\n• Tuition Reimbursement: $2,000 semi-annually ($4,000 aggregated over a full calendar year)\n• 0% interest Hardship Loan Program\n\nAbout the Data Engineer - AI and Data Operations - Remote\n\nThe AI and Data Operations team is responsible for providing accurate, timely, well-structured data to AI Engineers, Business Intelligence Engineers, and management teams. As a Data Engineer, you will build and maintain data repositories, custom workflows, data integrations, and imports. You will work closely with Business Intelligence and AI Engineers to create shared data models they can use to drive value for the business.\n\nWhat will you do?\n\nMonitor data processes, workflows, and jobs, and address any issues that arise\nLeverage SQL, Python, Azure tools, PowerBI, and other technologies to extract, transform, and load data into well-designed data models\nUnderstand and follow all rules and procedures required by security and best practice policies\nDocument data models and software, and clearly communicate current state and changes to the teams that use them\nDocument metadata in a centralized repository in a way that allows us to maximize the value of the data we manage\nWork with public and private APIs, file stores, databases, and other repositories to enhance and expand data capabilities\nWrite highly resilient, high throughput data workflows with solid logging and process monitoring\nImport and integrate data into front line systems for MarketStar corporate and client teams\nActively engage with the team while working in a remote environment, working to deliver an excellent level of service to all consumers of the data\nCreate and maintain highly reliable APIs that expose data and AI services to other teams\nConstantly improve yourself and the team through training and sharing of best practices\nUnderstand MarketStar’s business processes and make suggestions on data services that could drive value for the business\n\nDesired Attributes for Success:\n\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Engineering, or similar field\nA willingness to learn new tools and technologies\nExperience querying data using the SQL language\nExperience working with data using the Python language\nExperience creating and sharing data models/data marts/data warehouses\nExperience working with APIs\nA high-level understanding of sales processes and tools\nSolid communication skills with experience translating complex technical processes or problems to non-technical language\nExperience in measuring, reporting, and analysis of processes\nUnderstanding of agile project/task management techniques\n\n\nMarketStar does not discriminate in any aspect of employment based on race, color, religion, national origin, ancestry, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, age, veteran status, disability, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local employment discrimination laws where MarketStar does business.','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=31a7234bedb36191&fccid=c296b625cb8947e4&vjs=3','indeed'),(422,'Data Scientist','United States','Swire Coca-Cola USA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','Who is Swire Coca-Cola? We are one of the largest bottlers of Coca-Cola and other beverage brands in America. Our 7,200 hardworking and passionate employees produce and distribute more than 50 brands and flavors across 13 states. We have as many careers as we have flavors, and regardless of which role you choose, you have a direct impact on Swire Coca-Cola, our products, and the communities we call home.\nAt Swire Coca-Cola, our commitment to excellence is what guides our actions with our employees. We offer a comprehensive benefits package for full-time associates which includes: Medical, Dental, Vision, 401K, Paid Vacation, Paid Holidays and Company Discounts.\n\nWhat does a Data Scientist do at Swire Coca-Cola?\n\nAs Data Scientist, you will be responsible for conducting world-class data science and advanced analytics inclusive of modeling and AI/ML techniques across all channels, customer and consumer segments, markets, and products/categories. This role drives business value via actionable analytics in conjunction with Insight Strategy and Execution team.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nConducts analysis of data to identify insights and actions that could benefit or mitigate potential risks to the business.\nDevelop predictive models via machine learning methodologies for customer and consumer insights; leverage analytics to provide input into a clear, relevant, actionable, measurable, trusted view of the customer and consumer to support business needs.\nUnderstands and can communicate the effects of decisions to the business. Anticipates and explains the effects of decisions to inform business-facing team and influence key business partners.\nUnderstands the business and prioritizes analytics needs including allocating resources, funds and vets proposed analysis for high-impact or substantial projects affecting the capability. Manages business expectations around prioritization and provides transparency to the process.\nExecutes work effectively using established key processes.\nMaintains effective relationships with the key stakeholders and participants. Understands the dynamics of the processes and interests of the involved parties to reach effective agreements and resolutions.\nUnderstands key performance metrics (e.g., revenue and margin growth, consumer loyalty improvements and process and execution efficiencies).\nQualifications:\n\nAdvanced degree in STEM discipline (Science, Technology, Engineering or Mathematics or related field required\n8 years\' experience in analytics, business, or related area\n4 years\' project management experience\n4 years\' analytics, statistics and/or database knowledge and experience (using tools, applications, platforms, etc.)\n2 years\' executive leadership experience in a consumer insights function for a global consumer-oriented organization in retail, distribution, manufacturing, or a related industry preferred\nWorld class predictive analytics skillset including modeling, AI/ML, programming skills, and other advanced techniques. Understands and effectively utilizes analytics systems, databases, and tools.\nProficient in R, Python, SQL, or other programming language(s)\nAbility to identify new issues, trends, and opportunities from data\nWritten and verbal communication skills\nStrong customer service orientation\nUp to 25% travel with overnight stays\nSwire Coca-Cola, USA is an equal employment opportunity and affirmative action employer that participates in the E-Verify program as required by law. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, Veteran status or other legally protected characteristics.','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=b3b9070cb253753c&fccid=7c88dd3822fc77f7&vjs=3','indeed'),(423,'Senior Software Engineer, Data Scientist','United States','Qlik',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','What makes us Qlik\n\nQlik helps enterprises around the world move faster, work smarter, and lead the way forward with an end-to-end solution for getting value out of data. A Gartner Magic Quadrant Leader for 11 years in a row! Our platform is the only one on the market that allows for open-ended, curiosity-driven exploration, giving everyone – at any skill level – the ability to make real discoveries that lead to real outcomes and transformative changes. We are a Values-Driven organization, operating over 100 countries with 45,000 customers around the world. If you think we are interesting, please read on – we may be looking for you!\n\n\nSenior Software Engineer, Data Scientist\n\n\n\n\nJoin the team responsible for designing, creating, building, delivering and maintaining our AutoML platform, along with the infrastructure environment to support it. We are looking for a creative, motivated and dedicated individual with technical aptitude to join us in a Data Scientist and Software Engineer position to further the evolution of our world-class supervised machine learning platform The day-to-day work of this role is primarily software engineering; that is the nature of building a software platform. However, this role also requires a significant understanding of data science and machine learning fundamentals, tools, and best practices to ensure that features of the platform are implemented well. The successful candidate will have a strong analytical and mathematical background coupled with excellent communication and outstanding teamwork skills.\n\nResponsibilities include:\nWorking on the engineering team to help build the next generation of the company’s web services.\nLearning quickly while utilizing new tools/languages/frameworks/patterns/etc.\nProviding guidance on both software and product solutions on the application of statistics and machine learning.\n\n\nQualifications include:\n\nBachelor of Science degree in mathematics, statistics, engineering, data science, or equivalent. Master’s degree preferred.\n4 + years in data science with a strong understanding of supervised machine learning.\nGreat communication, attitude, and teamwork skills.\nAble to communicate machine learning concepts and help make pragmatic decisions.\nProficiency in Python.\nFamiliarity with event-driven software.\nSQL Experience.\nFamiliarity with GoLang, an asset.\nProficiency of the application of machine learning libraries and packages (ex. Pandas, scikit-learn).\nProficiency of the machine learning lifecycle: Problem framing, Data ingestion, Data preparation, Model fitting, Model assessment, Model application, Operationalization of results.\n\n\nLocation\nThe role is located in Salt Lake City, UT.\n\n\nAbout Qlik\nQlik Company Page – Who we are!\nOur Values at Qlik: Challenge, Take Responsibility, Move Fast, Be Open and Straightforward\nCompetitive Benefits package\nFlexible working environment\nGiving back is a part of our culture – we give you a day to change the world. In addition, we encourage our employees to participate in our Corporate Responsibility Employee Programs\nLearn about our Corporate Responsibility Program by visiting Qlik.org\nCheck out our careers in R&D here.\nCheck out our company page on Linkedin! &\nFollow us on Instagram @lifeatqlik and on Twitter @Qlik\nCheck us out on Youtube!\nQlik is an Equal Opportunity Employer and does not discriminate on the basis of any protected category or characteristic. We value the diversity of our workforce. If you need assistance due to disability during the application and/or recruiting process, please contact us via the Accessibility Request Form\n\nAGENCIES: Qlik is not accepting unsolicited assistance from search firms for this employment opportunity. Please, no phone calls or emails. All resumes submitted by search firms to any employee at Qlik via-email, the Internet or in any form and/or method without a valid written search agreement in place for this position will be deemed the sole property of Qlik. No fee will be paid in the event the candidate is hired by Qlik as a result of the referral or through other means.','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=680711c75e4f2788&fccid=49ad47b3debb43f4&vjs=3','indeed'),(424,'Data Scientist','United States','Black Rifle Coffee Company',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','WE ARE\nWe are Black Rifle Coffee Company, a veteran-owned company serving premium coffee to people who love America. We have a love for coffee, dogs, the outdoors, America, and most importantly, our customers! We are more than a product and more than a company; we are a culture. A culture full of motivated men and women who roll up their sleeves and get the job done with integrity, love, innovation, and radical transparency. Join us as we take action on our commitment to provide quality coffee and give back to the veteran and first responder communities and those who support it.\nTHE ROLE\nBlack Rifle Coffee Company is looking to bring on a Data Scientist. We are looking for a driven, ambitious individual who wants to create a career developing high impact analysis and solutions.\nYOUR TASK\n\nDevelop predictive models for customer acquisition, retention, cross-sell, lifetime value and marketing spend optimization\nImplement models on CRM platforms for marketing, ecommerce and customer contact efforts. Work closely with business owners to meet their requirements and ensure models are being used properly.\nMonitor model performance to verify algorithms are providing expected lift\nCollect, synthesize, and analyze data from multiple sources\nIdentify data and software needs. Drive customer data platform initiatives to optimize environment for analytics\nDocument queries, processes, and information assets\nIdentify and work to resolve any data quality issues\nHelp with a variety of other projects including customer analytics, subscription analytics, forecasting and reporting. This position will flex into multiple areas as needed.\n\nYOUR EXPERIENCE\n\nBachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science, or related field\nMaster’s in Data Analytics or similar quantitative field preferred\n1+ year of demonstrated data science experience\nPython / R / SQL experience required\nFamiliarity with analytic or cloud platforms such as BiqQuery, AWS or Azure\nProficient in creating reports and visualizations. Tableau, Looker, Google Data Studio (or similar).\nProficient in Google suite of products (Sheets, Slides, etc.) or similar.\nAbility to multi-task and take initiative, working both individually and as part of a team\nAbility to clearly communicate complex results to technical and non-technical audiences is critical\nExperience working with eCommerce, Customer Contact or Marketing data preferred\n\nYOUR BENEFITS\nCompetitive Pay-\nComprehensive medical, dental & vision package\n401k with company match\nCompany-paid life insurance + supplemental options\nShort and Long-Term disability options/coverage\nExtensive EAP program with legal coverage\nPro-deal discounts with corporate partners in outdoor equipment, clothing, etc.\nAmerican values-based culture built on freedom, integrity, accountability, respect, love, and commitment to serve those who have served.\n\nBRCC is an equal opportunity employer. Applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, sex, race, color, religion, national origin, genetics, disability, marital status, sexual orientation, veteran status or any other protected characteristic required by applicable law. All selected candidates will be required to submit to a pre-employment background check.\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nWork Location: Multiple Locations','https://indeed.com/company/Black-Rifle-Coffee-Company/jobs/Data-Scientist-e6211a634c033b35?fccid=3b9c7b6472687e0c&vjs=3','indeed'),(425,'Data Scientist','United States',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','Job Highlights\nSupports customer facing analyst team with advanced SQL query and data management expertise.\n\nConsistently display the ability to lead a variety of advanced analytic projects in tandem with a focus on helping to tell a compelling story with data and/or help to solve big problems for the institution, provider practice(s) and/or clinical enterprise.\n\nExpertise in industry leading statistical and data science practices; these enable operational improvement, strategy deployment, value improvement, and program advancement, and improved partner satisfaction and outcomes.\n\nData Visualizations\nCommunicates findings effectively, both visually and in plain language as to make them useful to non-analytic stakeholders\nCreate data visualizations that convey a full data story to the end user\nDetermine the best tool to use and best type of visual for a given set of data. Adopts new tools and techniques as needed.\nApply design best practices in a way that is visually appealing and draws the viewer in, while avoiding data representation practices that can mislead the viewer.\n\n\n\nPrimary Technologies Required\nProficient with standard office productivity tools, such as MS Office\nComprehensive understanding of statistical models\nProficient with SQL\nProficient with analytical scripting language (Python, R, Java etc.)\nExtra Credit for\nExperience with data visualizations.\nExperience and Mindset Needed\n5+ Years of experience as a Data Scientists\nBA/BS in a quantitative or computer science field\nFluency in SQL and a programming language\nA successful history of manipulating, processing and extracting value from large disconnected datasets.\nQuick learner - we face new challenges every day\nExpert in coding -we develop real products\nCompensation\nCompetitive Salary and Benefits (unlimited PTO)\nStock incentive program\nCareer plan and lifelong learning - We want you to grow in your role based on their curiosity, passion, and ability to learn and evolve\nZartico is a Work From Anywhere company. This role is available to candidates in all states in the U.S. and there is no commute necessary! You will be working from your home or home office from any location in the US you choose. Our HQ is in Salt Lake City, Utah, and working at HQ is always an option as well.','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=1c613ae51e0fbebc&fccid=dd616958bd9ddc12&vjs=3','indeed'),(426,'Research Data Scientist II','United States','ARUP Laboratories',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Utah','Job Details\n\nDescription\n\nSchedule:\nMonday - Friday (40 hrs/wk)\n8:00 AM - 5:00 PM\n\n\n\n\nDepartment: Biocomputing - 331\n\nPrimary Purpose:\n\nThe Research Data Scientist develops methods and tools for gathering, storing, manipulating, analyzing, and displaying research and clinical data. The position supports design and implementation of tools and process analyses from a variety of research and clinical testing methods with the goal to advance the state-of-the-art in clinical diagnosis, treatment, data analysis, and reporting. This position will address the critical needs of research and clinical organizations seeking scalability and flexibility for a variety of applications in the field of laboratory medicine.\n\nAbout ARUP:\n\nARUP Laboratories is a national clinical and anatomic pathology reference laboratory and an enterprise of the University of Utah and its Department of Pathology. Based in Salt Lake City, Utah.\n\nARUP proudly hires top talent to create a work environment of diversity, professional growth and continuous development. Our workforce is committed to the important service we provide to over one million patients each month. We always strive for excellence and have a strong desire to have involvement with the advances in medicine and the role laboratory services plays within each patient’s life. We never forget that there is a patient behind every specimen we receive.\n\nWe are looking for individuals who want to contribute to ARUP\'s culture of accountability, integrity, service, and excellence. Consider joining our dynamic team.\n\nEssential Functions:\n\nCreates, refines and validates software, data analysis processes, statistical, and data visualization tools.\n\nImplements and maintains computational tools for data mining and data integration.\n\nDevelops enhanced data collection procedures to include information that is relevant for building analytic systems and reporting clinical results.\n\nDevelops new tools to aid in the analysis of assay quality metrics, interpretation, and reporting.\n\nDevelops novel methods/algorithms, and extends, adapts and improves existing methods as needed.\n\nDevelops analysis approaches in support of clinical applications.\n\nWorks effectively with other scientists, programmers, engineers, and researchers to implement novel or adapt existing approaches to data analysis and reporting.\n\nSupports transition of developed software and analysis into clinical practice.\n\nProvides consultative support to clinical and research staff, pathology residents, Medical Directors and others as assigned.\n\nOther duties as assigned.\n\nPhysical and Other Requirements:\n\nStooping: Bending body downward and forward by bending spine at the waist.\n\nReaching: Extending hand(s) and arm(s) in any direction.\n\nMobility: The person in this position needs to occasionally move between work sites and inside the office to access file cabinets, office machinery, etc.\n\nCommunicate: Frequently and effectively communicate with others.\n\nPPE: Biohazard laboratory environment that requires use of personal protective equipment in accordance with CDC and OSHA regulations and company policies.\n\nARUP Policies and Procedures: To conduct self in compliance with all ARUP Policies and Procedures.\n\nSedentary Work: Exerting up to 10 pounds of force occasionally and/or negligible amount of force frequently or constantly to lift, carry, push, pull or otherwise move objects.\n\nQualifications\n\nEducation\n\nRequired\n\nMaster\'s Degree or better in Life Sciences or related field.\n\nPreferred\n\nPhD or better in Life Sciences or related field.\n\nExperience\n\nRequired\n\nMaster\'s Degree in a Life or Health or Lab Science field, Computer Science, or relevant technical field\nDemonstrated experience with statistics\nAbility to collaborate in a cross-functional environment\nExperience in data mining or machine learning\nFive (5) years’ experience working with one of the following programming languages: Python, Java, C#, Javascript, R\nTwo (2) years’ experience with a machine learning framework such as PyTorch, Tensorflow, Keras, JAX or similar\nDemonstrated experience working in Linux environment\n\nPreferred\n\nPhD Degree in a Life or Health or Lab Science field, Computer Science, or relevant technical field\nTwo (2) years of experience in software development\nTwo (2) years of previous scientific programming or tool development experience\nExperience working with the following technologies: Bash or similar linux shell, git/github, SQL/NoSQL databases\n\nEqual Opportunity Employer/Protected Veterans/Individuals with Disabilities\n\nThe contractor will not discharge or in any other manner discriminate against employees or applicants because they have inquired about, discussed, or disclosed their own pay or the pay of another employee or applicant. However, employees who have access to the compensation information of other employees or applicants as a part of their essential job functions cannot disclose the pay of other employees or applicants to individuals who do not otherwise have access to compensation information, unless the disclosure is (a) in response to a formal complaint or charge, (b) in furtherance of an investigation, proceeding, hearing, or action, including an investigation conducted by the employer, or (c) consistent with the contractor’s legal duty to furnish information. 41 CFR 60-1.35(c)','https://indeed.com/rc/clk?jk=874b5be6474c9e61&fccid=5a0c54e883c4c5e6&vjs=3','indeed'),(427,'Data Scientist','United States','Pharmscript',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'New-Jersey','Job Description:\n\nPharmScript is one of the nation’s leading pharmacies, partnering with long-term and post- acute care facilities to supply medications to thousands of residents and patients. When you join the PharmScript family, you join the ranks of more than 1,700 dedicated people across the country who help to get safe, accurate, and timely medication to those who need it most.\n\nWe’re looking for a Data Scientist to join our PharmScript team within our Continuous Improvement department. As the Data Scientist, the ideal candidate will leverage the disparate datasets, ensuring data integrity and quality, creating innovative solutions and providing operational insights to improve quality, service and customer experience. The ideal candidate will have experience with database technologies, operational analytics, working knowledge of Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning (AI/ML) techniques.\n\nThis role will require deep acquaintance with PharmScript\'s data, including but not limited to patient, payor, claims, and dispensing. You will play a key role in ensuring data integrity, accuracy and quality as the foundation for PharmScript’s data-centric AI journey. You will collaborate with internal customers to design, develop, validate, implement, maintain, enhance and support analytical and machine learning models to deliver actionable insights that can be incorporated into business strategies and program development. The ideal candidate for this role will have strong coding skills, a passion for creating technology to improve health care, an attitude of creativity and continual learning and a desire to teach others.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nCollaborate with stakeholders, both technical and non-technical, throughout the organization to identify opportunities for leveraging company data to drive business solutions.\nPerform data acquisition and data transformation in support of AI/ML projects\nDevelop analytical and machine learning models based on patient, payor, claims, and dispensing data to deliver business insights.\nDevelop processes and tools to monitor and analyze model performance and be responsible for implementing robust testing strategies leading to model optimization.\nAssess the integrity, accuracy and quality of data sources and data collection techniques.\nDefine the data science development workflows from coding and architecture best practices, data strategy, to ML training and Inference platforms.\nKeep up to date, latest developments in AI/ML and incorporate these in our best practices.\nDevelop presentations around insights to be delivered to business users at all levels: strategic, tactical, operational, and across functions.\nEnsure that AI/ML deliverables can be productionized and integrated into existing systems, processes and application development.\nAnalyze and evaluate large quantities of data in relational databases and unstructured forms of data, effectively balancing quality, availability and timeliness.\nAssist various departments with evaluating AI/ML solutions or software capabilities on the market.\n\nQualifications:\n\nMaster’s degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering or a relevant field required.\n2+ years of experience in building, training and deployment of AI/ML models including deep learning.\n2+ years of experience in database and data modeling design, data quality principles, source file data extraction, complex data transformation and load processes.\n2+ years’ experience in systems analysis, data analysis and requirements gathering in healthcare industry experience is preferred.\nExperience using statistical computer languages (R, Python, etc.) to manipulate data, develop analytical models and draw insights from large datasets.\nDemonstrated experience with the lifecycle development process for AI and ML models including requirements analysis, design, coding, testing, debugging, implementation and support.\nExperience with cloud AI/ML platform such as AWS, Google Cloud or Azure preferred.\nExperience with collaborating with cross functional teams and stakeholders within a division and enterprise-wide to evaluate new AI/ML opportunities.\nThorough understanding of how to interpret operational data and translate business needs into technical design and requirements.\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills, and the ability to interact professionally with a diverse group of peers, managers, executives, and subject matter experts to uncover and effectively present insights that inform strategic decisions.\nHave capability and desire to mentor others and educate business users on AI/ML knowledge.\nAbility to adapt in a dynamic work environment, learn quickly, solve problems and make decisions with minimal supervision.\nSolid project management skills and capability of managing multiple deliverables and meet deadlines.\n\nEEO Statement:\n\nPharmScript is fully committed to employing a diverse workforce. We recruit and retain talented individuals without regard to gender, race, age, marital status, disability, veteran status, sexual orientation and gender identity or any other status protected by federal, state or local law.\n\nEO/Minorities/Females/Disabled/Veterans','https://indeed.com/pagead/clk?mo=r&ad=-6NYlbfkN0BNT_5o3cfLrb7ir7K4bhXiFPvWzjMfEhw3LdDDFkfdybKU4fl9FoRWLppKpZlDx96Api_mqU-TZWaC2YT7g-_sittnnDFc0vepz0vbOH_cDJ0M_3duXpAZuew8ogg4Vjx9Bqjx3952YUVOKufCQh-A2Cm4D-gx24lhOHdBXvDZiUl0qE93Nh2nT0loi72KTydTq7tTdMAsK2EJ3','indeed'),(428,'Data Scientist','United States','PCS Wireless',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'New-Jersey','This role is onsite in Florham Park, NJ.\n\nAs a Data Scientist in PCS Wireless’ Data, Analytics and Reporting team, you’ll get to build pricing analysis using scores of data from multiple data sources, analyze real business issues, dive into 1,000s of SKUs to improve inventory, margins and help drive the most critical KPIs of the business.\n\nAbout You\n\nYou are a problem solver excited to take on complex data challenges. You love learning new technologies almost as much as you love mastering those you already know. You thrive in environments where data leads, the customers are global, and the stakes are high. You choose to work where you can get your hands dirty and make a real impact.\n\nAbout Us\n\nPCS Wireless is the global leader in the secondary market for connected devices. PCS Wireless partners with manufacturers, operators, distributors, service centers, and retailers to turn inventory challenges into business opportunities. We specialize in the responsible and profitable redistribution of new and pre-owned phones, tablets, accessories, and other wireless equipment. PCS Wireless’ partners leverage our Asset Recovery, Buyback Programs, OEM Value Added Distribution, Open Market Programs, Device Services and Device Diagnostics to improve their bottom line.\n\nAbout the role\n\nReporting to the Controller, Data, Analytics and Reporting, you will build data models that drive pricing floors, profitability analysis, inventory depreciation regressions, customer and supplier analysis:\n\nAnalyze SKUs to determine depreciation rates and primary depreciation drivers.\nProject pricing floors for inventory management leveraging existing sales, auction and third-party data sources coupled with depreciation rates, predicted turns and cost of capital.\nPerform supplier analysis to determine most valuable supplier sources.\nCreate customer models to inform sales teams of highest margin / SKU sales opportunities by customer, geography, sector\nImplement continuous data enhancement models to improve prediction accuracy.\nBuild out AI/RPA platforms\n\nWhat you need\n\nSelf-starter & Independent critical thinker\nBSc or higher in statistics, computer science, mathematics, or a simil